# Simple LAN Chat (Flask)

A minimal internal chat website that runs on Ubuntu and is accessible to any device on the same LAN.

- Backend: Python 3 + Flask
- Database: SQLite (file `chat.db` in the project folder)
- Frontend: Pure HTML + CSS + JavaScript
- Single shared chat room
- Optional username (stored in browser session)
- Auto-scroll and polling every 2 seconds for new messages
- No external services, no accounts

---

## Project Structure

```text
chat_app/
  app.py
  models.py
  requirements.txt
  README.md
  chat.db                (auto-created on first run)
  templates/
    chat.html
  static/
    style.css


## Installation
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-venv python3-pip
mkdir -p ~/chat_app
cd ~/chat_app
# Copy all project files here (app.py, models.py, requirements.txt, templates/, static/)
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
cd ~/chat_app
source venv/bin/activate
python app.py


## access from other devices
hostname -I -->find server's lan ip address on ubuntu
on other devices: http://192.168.1.42:5000

## to clear all messages:
in app.py change flag and password
restart the app
Then you can send a POST request to http://<server-ip>:5000/admin/clear with form data password=<your-strong-password>
curl -X POST -F "password=your-strong-password" http://192.168.1.42:5000/admin/clear
